Preparatory stage Cube device
Centers (6 pcs.) They never change their position relative to each other and always remain in their place, that is, in the cube there will always be a pattern: opposite the white center will be yellow, opposite the blue - green, and opposite red - orange. The color of the center, respectively, is the color of the assembled side (blue center ➝ blue side, etc.). Ribs (12 pcs.) The edges of the cube have two colors and form a kind of \"cross\" when it is in place. These colors cannot be separated. Corners (8 pcs.) Corner elements consist of 3 colors. These colors also cannot be disconnected among themselves.
Sides
Sides of the Rubik\'s Cube - 9 elements that can be rotated simultaneously.\n\nAlgorithms will help us to collect the cube. An apostrophe, or as it is called speedcubers \"stroke\" means that the movement should be performed counterclockwise. In order not to get confused, imagine that you are looking at the rotating side in front of you.\n\nНапример: \n\n— R it is turning the right side clockwise.\n— R\' it is turning the right side counterclockwise
Right side\nMove R Right side\nMove R\' Left side\nMove L Left side\nMove L\' Move U Move U\' Move D Move D\' Move F Move F\' Move B Move B\' Stage 1. Сorrect cross Flower
We divide the assembly of the correct cross into two steps, the first step is the "flower", which then turns into the right cross in the second step. Our goal is to collect a flower in which the center is yellow, and the petals are white (pic 1). During assembly, hold the cube with the yellow center up. \n\nWhen the flower is ready, we will replace the yellow center with white to remake it into the correct cross. (pic. 2) Flower Cross
To create a flower, we need to find all 4 white edges and raise them to the yellow center. It is very easy to do. You can do this intuitively and go straight to the next step. Result
1. If we see white on the middle layer, then simply lift it with a movement \"R\". Do this with all the edges on the middle layer. 1. Lift R
2. If there is an edge on the middle layer, but another part interferes with delivering it, we move the part that interferes with us with the movement U and put the necessary one in its place with the movement R. 2. Do U R
Details on the middle layer are over. Go to the bottom. 3. If the part we need looks white down, then simply raise it with two movements R, which is written in the formulas R2. 3. Do R2
4. If the part is on the upper or lower layer and looks white at you (Pic. 4 or 5), then first you need to move the part to the middle layer by moving F, and then put the part from the middle layer in its place (if it is occupied by another part, move by its motion U or U\'). 4. F U L\' 5. F U\' R
Congratulations! If you managed to collect the flower, then the following stages of assembling the cube will not cause you any difficulties. The flower is the hardest to understand among beginners.
Cross It is very simple and in just a few movements, the flower can be turned into a regular cross. We look at the flower and pay attention to the color of the rib. Choose any of the edges, combine it with the center of the same color and lower it down (make the movement F2). We do this in turn with all the ribs. F2 When the ribs end, turn the entire cube over and see that the white regular cross is assembled. Please note that the color of the edges in the cross should match the colors of the centers. If you suddenly get the wrong cross, try again! True cross Bad Cross
Stage 2. The first layer Corners No corners With corners Next we will collect the corners, (3 colors on the element), as a result, the whole first layer should be obtained. But first, we will learn a very simple but effective formula called bang-bang. Consists of 4 movements R U R\' U\', in simple words: up-left-down-right.
Pic.1 Pic.2 Move our assembled regular cross down (Pic. 1). We are looking for a corner on the top layer, with white color. (Pic. 2)
R U R\' U\' If, for example, the angle is green-red, then we put it between the green and the red center, we perform a bang-bang.
(R U R\' U\')x3 Depending on the situation, bang-bang must be performed from 1 to 5 times, if for example a corner looks white up, then you need to perform 3 times.
(R U R\' U\')x2 If you notice that the corner is in place, but you also need to expand it, we use a bang-bang. Twist until the corner is correct.
R U R\' U\' But, if you were unlucky and the corners with white ended on the top layer, you need to beat a corner with one bang-bang, which stands in the wrong place and continue to be arranged in the usual way. Congratulations, the first layer is assembled!
Stage 3. The middle layer
To collect the second layer, you need to take turns to put the edges from the top layer to the middle. To do this, we need to learn the bang-bang with the left hand L\' U\' L U or in other words with the left hand we do up-right-down-left One layer Two layers
The edge goes to the right. We pay special attention to colors. For example, take the green-red rib. We bring it up and put it in red to the red center and hold the cube in red to ourselves (Pic. 1). Do U R U R\' U\' y L\' U\' L U y means intercepting the cube to the right. In our case, the green center will be in front of us. In words, the formula will sound like this: right bang-bang, interception to the right, left bang-bang. Pic. 1
The edge goes to the left If you substitute a green-red edge to the green center (Pic. 2), we can notice that this time the edge goes to the left. So we will do U\' L\' U\' L U y\' R U R\' U\' y\' means intercepting the cube to the left. In our case, the red center will be in front of us. In words, the formula will sound like this: left bang-bang, interception to the left, right bang-bang. Pic. 2
Ribs are over If you are unlucky and the necessary edges have ended on the top layer, and the second layer is not assembled - no problem! We put an incorrectly assembled edge on the right (Pic. 3) and do R U R\' U\' y L\' U\' L U The words are as follows: the right bang-bang, the interception to the right (the green center in front of you), the left bang-bang and then we usually arrange the ribs. Congratulations, after arranging all the edges in the second layer, the cube is 60 percent assembled. Less than half comes to this stage, so if you succeed, then you are well done and soon your Rubik\'s cube will be collected. Pic. 3
Stage 4. Edges of the last layer
Yellow cross
We have almost collected the cube. Just a little bit left. At this stage, we again flip the cube yellow up. The sequence for creating a yellow cross is as follows: \npoint → half a cross (nine hours) → stick → cross You can already have a whole cross assembled on a cube. But not always so lucky. Sometimes, nevertheless, you get one sad point, which you need to turn gradually into a cross. Point Half cross (nine hours)
Whatever figure you have, we do F R U R\' U\' F\'. Simply put F (bang-bang) F\'. Please note that if you have \"the floor of the cross\", then you need to hold it for 9 hours, so that one arrow looks to the left, and the second - up. And if the stick, then hold it horizontally and only then do the algorithm. If you originally had a point, then it will turn into a half cross, if there was a half cross, then they will turn into a stick, and if a stick, then into a cross. Attention!\nIf you have 1 or 3 elements looking up at the same time and you do not see any of the figures shown, your cube could be disassembled into parts and incorrectly assembled (by accident or with the aim of playing a trick). In this case, you will not collect the cube according to the formulas. We strongly recommend - disassemble the cube into parts and assemble it according to the colors mechanically. Stick Cross
Right yellow cross
The cross that turned out may be wrong (Pic. 1). We need to make sure that all the colors on the edges of the cross (3 layers) coincide with the centers (Pic. 2). Attention, we can have only three situations: \n1. edges coincide near \n2. edges coincide opposite \n3. you are lucky, and the cross is right or you just need to tighten the top layer. Pic.1 Pic.2
1. edges coincide next \nIf these two edges are adjacent - put them on the right and back, we make the formula R U R\' U R U2 R\' U, you should get the right cross (the color of the edges of the cross coincides with the centers. Nearby
2. edges coincide opposite \nIf these two edges coincide opposite - put them in front of us and behind, we make the formula R U R\' U R U2 R\', you should get the previous situation (Nearby). Opposite Nearby
Stage 5. Corner placement of the third layer First you need to check how many corners are in place. This is either all, 1 corner or not a single one. If all the corners are in place, skip this step and move on to the next. \n\nThe corners can look yellow in any direction. The main thing is that the orange-green corner stands between the orange and green center, the green-red corner stands between green and red, etc. If there are no such angles, then we make an algorithm:\nR U\' L\' U R\' U\' L U\n\nAfter the execution of the algorithm, 1 correct angle should appear. We put it on the left and on the top (where the thumb of the left hand is) and do the same algorithm. If all else fails, again put in the lower left point and repeat.\n\nAttention!\nIf you have only 2 or 3 elements in place, your cube was disassembled into parts and incorrectly assembled. From this state, the cube cannot be assembled using the formulas. Disassemble the cube into parts and assemble it according to the colors mechanically.\n\nWhen all the corners stand in their place, all that remains is to deploy them to completely assemble the cube. Zero corners in place One corner in place
Final stage. Corners orientation. We’ll be turning corners with bang-bang(R U R\' U\'). This is a simple formula that you already know very well! Check once again that all corners are in place (Pic. 1). Intercept the cube so that the corners to be assembled were from below (Pic. 2). We start from any unassembled corner and make bang-bangs until the corner is assembled. (Pic. 3) \nThen twist the bottom layer, and substitute the next unfolded corner (Fig. 4). We continue to make bang-bangs until the 2nd corner is assembled (Pic. 5) and so on. \n\nATTENTION! If the corner is already assembled, you still need to finish the bang-bang to the end, and only then proceed to the next. \nWhen you expand all the corners, the cube will be assembled, do not forget to tighten the last movement.\n\nWarning\nIt’s easiest to stumble somewhere. Therefore, carefully, otherwise the cube will have to be re-assembled. Pic. 1 Pic. 2 Pic. 3 Pic. 4 Pic. 5
Congratulations! You are well done. You managed to collect your first Rubik\'s Cube.\nTell this to your friends.
